# Ent preload

Manifest-driven agent ops kit (not an app). CLI: `node ent/tools/ent.mjs`. Contract: `ent/ent.manifest.yaml`. Dynamic snapshot: `.ent/session-context.md`.

## Layout

| Zone | Path | Role |
|------|------|------|
| Immutable core | `ent/` | Kit — `git pull` only; keep git clean |
| Mutable ring | `content/`, `.ent/`, `.env` | Project work, audit, credentials |
| Projected config | `.cursor/` | From `ent sync` — edit `ent/agent-adapters/` templates |

Open **workspace root** (parent of `ent/`), not `ent/` alone — fails `core.workspace_open_mode`. MCP loads from consumer `.cursor/mcp.json`.

**Multi-root dev:** consumer fixture = ops start point; kit repo = product edits. Session hook writes `.ent/session-context.md` on the consumer root with paths.

## Workflows

**Onboard** (`/ent-onboard` when `.ent/state.json` missing): `onboard` (or `scaffold` → `audit` → `render-onboard`)

```bash
node ent/tools/ent.mjs onboard --workspace-root .
```

**Offboard** (`/ent-offboard`): disconnect MCP + clear onboard state — `offboard --dry-run` first

```bash
node ent/tools/ent.mjs offboard --workspace-root . --dry-run
```

**Update ent:** `git -C ent pull` → sync → audit

## Extension map

| Adding… | Start | Also |
|---------|-------|------|
| Audit check | `ent/ent.manifest.yaml`, `ent/tools/lib/audit.mjs` | `ent/docs/TESTING.md` |
| Profile | `ent/ent.manifest.yaml` | copy `wordpress_mcp` |
| Cursor rules/hooks | `ent/agent-adapters/cursor/workspace-template/.cursor/` | `ent/tools/lib/sync.mjs` |
| Skill | `ent/agent-adapters/shared/skills/` | → `.cursor/skills/` |
| WP MCP | `ent/tools/run-wordpress-mcp.mjs` | `ent/tools/lib/wp-smoke.mjs` |

Check IDs and phases: `.ent/session-context.md`.

## Audit

- **fail** — fix; **skip** — deferred (**skip ≠ pass**)
- Clean audit (zero fail, zero skip) → `.ent/state.json`

## Docs

`AGENTS.md` · `ent/docs/EXECUTION.md` · `ent/docs/TESTING.md` · `ent/PLAN.md`

## Anti-patterns

- Edit workspace `.cursor/` — edit templates + sync
- Mutable work inside `ent/` · commit `.env`
